<paragraph blockId="7.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,312,448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">
Based on the newly examined material, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[680,824,312,339]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatatus">
<emphasis box="[680,824,312,339]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Q. dilatatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded for the first time from Middle Asia (
<collectingCountry box="[197,341,349,376]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
). It is a widely distributed Palaearctic species that had already been recorded from several provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[342,420,385,411]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Russia</collectingCountry>
near the border with 
<collectingCountry box="[671,808,385,411]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Salnitska M. &amp; Solodovnikov A." box="[823,1205,385,412]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref9088" refString="Salnitska M. &amp; Solodovnikov A. 2019 Rove beetles of the genus Quedius (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) of Russia: a key to species and annotated catalogue. ZooKeys 847: 1 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 847.34049" type="journal article" year="2019">Salnitska &amp; Solodovnikov 2019</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" box="[303,442,422,448]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatatus">
<emphasis box="[303,442,422,448]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Q. dilatatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Altai Mountains.
</paragraph>
